JSE-listed Huge Group on Tuesday reported expectations of a 55% to 70% rise in earnings per share (EPS) to between 26.5c and 29.07c for the six months ended August 31, against the EPS of 17.1c apiece in the comparative period last year. Headline earnings per share (HEPS) are expected to increase by between 40% and 55%, to 26.74c to 29.6c, compared with the HEPS of 19.1c posted in the first half of last year.